snippet.description:

'100 Million' is an ode to the unparalleled success achieved by DIVINE and Karan Aujla. This track not only celebrates their achievements but also stands as an anthem, for those with grand dreams. Synopsis:
Militant activities are going out of control in the Srinagar Valley, so a new and elite unit, Air Dragons, is commissioned by the Air Headquarters. They are now the first responders to any hostile activity. They comprise of the best combat aviators handpicked from across the IAF. FIGHTER is the story of Air Dragons who are willing to give it their all for the nation while going through the highs and lows of their internal and external battles.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: 2nd T20I | Sri Lanka vs Zimbabwe | Highlights | 16th January 2024
snippet.description:

Click here to watch all highlights: https://bit.ly/3OVl9LM

Click here to watch more: https://www.sonyliv.com/sports/cricket-zimbabwe-tour-of-sri-lanka-1700001364

Click here to subscribe now: https://bit.ly/3Q78rHU

Zimbabwe won the toss and decided to bowl first in the 2nd T20I. Sri Lanka lost their top three batters for one-digit scores but later Charith Asalanka and Angelo Mathews stitched up a brilliant partnership. Sri Lanka ended with a total of 173 runs and Zimbabwe then came into bat. Opener Craig Ervine played a superb knock worth 70 runs while Luke Jongwe and Clive Madande's heroics ultimately took Zimbabwe to a thrilling four-wicket victory.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

snippet.title: Main ATAL Hoon (Trailer 2) | Pankaj Tripathi | Ravi Jadhav | Vinod Bhanushali | 19 Jan 2024
snippet.description:
More than a poet. More than a statesman. More than a Prime Minister. Presenting trailer 2 of #MainATALHoon. 

Vinod Bhanushali presents, Main ATAL Hoon, a film on the extraordinary life of the leader you knew but the man you didn't, starring National Award winner Pankaj Tripathi. 

Directed by National Awardee Ravi Jadhav, and written by Rishi Virmani and Ravi Jadhav, "Main ATAL Hoon" produced by Bhanushali Studios Limited and Legend Studios, is produced by Vinod Bhanushali, Sandeep Singh, and Kamlesh Bhanushali.

The film releases on 19th January 2024 in cinemas near you. 


CREDITS:

Starring : Pankaj Tripathi
Director : Ravi Jadhav
Producers : Vinod Bhanushali, Sandeep Singh and Kamlesh Bhanushali
Co Producer - Bhavesh Bhanushali, Sam Khan

BGM : Monty Sharma

snippet.title: 2024 Hyundai Creta vs Kia Seltos - Best SUV Under 20 Lacs | ICN Studio
snippet.description: We finally got the opportunity to test the 2024 Hyundai Creta and we pitted it against the Seltos Facelift. Fortunately, we had the diesel AT versions of both the cars that get the same 1.5-litre CRDi diesel engine mated to a 6-speed torque converter. Which one's better in terms of features, ride quality, handling and other attributes, we tell you in this detailed comparison.

snippet.title: Manipur Commando Killed After Suspected Kuki Militants Launch Bombs, Rocket-Propelled Grenade
snippet.description:
A Manipur police commando was shot dead, allegedly by militants, in Moreh town on January 17. The slain commando has been identified as W. Somorjit. Militants fired rocket-propelled grenades on a camp of the commandos, near Ward 7 of Moreh. While one commando died, another sustained injuries, an official said. A government official aware of the matter said, "The gunfight lasted for almost an hour. The situation is tense." Watch this video to know more.

snippet.title: Ayodhya Dispute Explained | Ram Mandir ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§µ‡§æ‡§Æ‡§™‡§Ç‡§•‡•Ä ‡§á‡§§‡§ø‡§π‡§æ‡§∏‡§ï‡§æ‡§∞‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§æ‡§ú‡§º‡§ø‡§∂ | ‡§Ö‡§Ø‡•ã‡§ß‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§µ‡§ø‡§µ‡§æ‡§¶ | RJ Raunak
snippet.description:
----------------------------------------
In this insightful video, we delve deep into the labyrinth of the Ram Janmabhoomi dispute, a contentious issue that has gripped the socio-political landscape of India for decades. Our focus centers on the report submitted by four historians ‚Äì R. S. Sharma, M. Athar Ali, D. N. Jha, and Suraj Bhan ‚Äì to the Home Ministry on May 13, 1991. This report claimed that the worship of Lord Ram in Ayodhya began only 300 years ago, depicting Ayodhya as a mystical city and characterizing Bhagwan Ram as a mere imaginative figure.

The video meticulously explores the role of this controversial report in the legal battles surrounding the Ram Janmabhoomi dispute. The historians' assertions were frequently cited by the Muslim side in the court, adding complexity to an already intricate matter. However, the turning point came in 2020 when the Supreme Court of India unequivocally rejected the report, delivering a verdict that questioned its credibility in no uncertain terms.

Our presentation unravels the layers of this historical controversy, shedding light on the implications of the rejected report and its impact on the legal proceedings. We highlight the significance of the Supreme Court's harsh rejection, bringing into question the reliability of the historians' claims and establishing a precedent for the narrative surrounding Ayodhya's history.

A substantial portion of the video is dedicated to the celebration of these historians by the left-leaning intellectuals, including notable figures like Irfan Habib. We meticulously showcase how these scholars shaped the discourse around the Ram Janmabhoomi issue, and the repercussions of their narrative on public opinion.

To bolster our argument, we draw on historical evidence from foreign visitors of the 16th and 17th centuries. These accounts, which have been largely overlooked, endorse the fact that Lord Ram was worshipped in Ayodhya during this period. By presenting these foreign perspectives, we aim to counter the claims made by the controversial historians and emphasize the deep-rooted historical connection of Ayodhya with the worship of Lord Ram.

Our video is a thought-provoking exploration of the intersection between history, religion, and politics. We navigate through the intricacies of the Ram Janmabhoomi dispute, unraveling the complexities woven by the controversial historians and dissecting their impact on the legal proceedings. Join us on this journey as we critically examine the multifaceted layers of one of India's most polarizing historical debates.

Mannat Murad Last Episode 33 - [Eng Sub] - Iqra Aziz - Talha Chahour - Digitally Presented by Jhalak Beauty Cream - 16th January 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Mannat Murad Digitally Digitally Presented by Jhalak Beauty Cream

Mannat is a beautiful young girl who hails from a progressive family that values love, care, and mutual respect. Raised in an environment where everyone's choices are respected, Mannat enjoys the freedom to make her own decisions. Following the untimely demise of her parents, she finds support from her elder brother, Nafees, who showers her with affection.

On the other hand, Murad belongs to a conservative family where his mother, the matriarch, wields significant influence over his life choices. As the only son, Murad is burdened with the responsibility of fulfilling his family's expectations. Soft-spoken and romantic by nature, Murad finds himself unable to defy his mother's authority, especially after the passing of his father.

Despite their starkly contrasting backgrounds, Mannat and Murad's hearts find solace in each other's presence, and they fall deeply in love. However, their families' interference creates misunderstandings between Mannat and Murad, testing the strength of their bond.

Will their families agree to their union? Will Mannat's family, with their open-mindedness, find common ground with Murad's conservative household? Can Mannat and Murad's love for each other withstand the motives of their families, who seek to create further misunderstandings between them?

Get ready for an ultimate showdown and witness the relentless pursuit of dreams as Prashant and Jimmy, face the world head-on to achieve success on their own terms in the finale episode of 1 Finance presents Sapne Vs Everyone - A TVF Original Series

The stakes are higher than ever as Prashant battles against time and destiny to fulfill his dream of becoming the lead actor, all before the clock runs out on his ill mother. Meanwhile, Jimmy goes all out to settle the score against Mamaji with a risky plan that could potentially be his downfall. 
Get ready for the finale you've been waiting for ‚Äì a symphony of ambition, courage, and sapne!

As an arm of the Marwadi Chandarana Group, 1 Finance is reimagining the space of personal finance advisory: https://1finance.onelink.me/5Kxt/tvfytsep6 
Through the expertise of our qualified financial advisors, we guide you towards tranquillity by offering hyper-personalised and unbiased advice, empowering you to attain a state of financial well-being.

Rate Us On IMDb: https://www.imdb.com/title/tt30263074/?ref_=ext_shr_lnk 

A TVF Original Series
Directed and Written By: Ambrish Verma
Produced By: Arunabh Kumar
Executive Producer: Vijay Koshy, Vaibhav Bundhoo, Pranav Thakker
Cast: Ambrish Verma, Paramvir Singh Cheema, Naveen Kasturia, Vijayant Kohli, Vaisakh Shankar

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.
